gomodel:SYNGO_2256  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.9: \"On transfection of γ2-/- neurons with the γ2 subunit (9E10γ-γ-γ) or with the 9E10α-γ-γ chimeric construct, the mIPSC frequency was restored to values similar to the wild-type control, consistent with restoration of function and postsynaptic localization of GABAA receptors. Consistent with normal immunoreactivity for GAD (Fig. 1B) and the vesicular inhibitory amino acid transporter (Schweizer e al., 2003) in γ2-/- neurons, efficient rescue of mIPSCs in transfected γ2-/- pyramidal cells confirmed that presynaptic function of GABAergic γ2-/- neurons was intact and that the functional deficit of GABAergic γ2-/- neurons was limited to the postsynaptic apparatus.\". Experimental description: - \"Cortical neurons were generated from γ2 subunit-deficient embryonic day 14.5 embryos generated by crossing of γ2+/- mice on a...\"\n- Overexpressed protein is of mouse species: \"The mouse γ2S (γ2) subunit cDNA ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_2256" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

